"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code sets the x-ticks and x-tick labels to unique dates from the DataFrame before setting the major locator and formatter for the x-axis. This can lead to inconsistencies in the x-axis ticks and labels. The x-ticks and labels should be set after configuring the major locator and formatter.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17,18c17,18\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator())\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%Y-%m'))\\n> ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n> ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\"\n}"